        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Familial generalized lentiginosis is a rare inherited skin hyperpigmentation disorder characterized by widespread lentigines without associated noncutaneous abnormalities. Patients present multiple brown to dark brown non-elevated macula of 0.2 to 1 cm in diameter spread over the entire body sometimes including palms or soles but never oral mucosa."
        },
